Enjoy this healthier version of “Kurkuri Bhindi “ made in @balzano_in Air Fryer 😍😋

Recipe:
Bhindi/okra - 25 nos.
Besan - 1 cup
Rice flour - 1/4 cup
Turmeric - 1/2 tsp
Kashmiri chilli powder - 1 tsp
Coriander powder - 1 tsp
Amchur - 1 tsp
Garam masala - 1/2 tsp
Salt to taste
Oil - 1 tbsp

For garnish:
Coriander leaves
chat masala
Lemon wedges

Method:
1. Wash and pat dry okra until all trace of water is removed.
2. Cut the top and bottom off of the bhindi.
3. Cut each okra into 8 pieces lengthwise. Now add all the spice powder along with salt & oil.
4. Sprinkle 2 tsp water.
Mix well to coat and set it aside for a few minutes to make the okra absorb the flavors.
5. Pre- heat the Air fryer using the preset option in the display panel or at 200c for 10 minutes.
6. Evenly place the bhindi in the Air fryer basket.
7. Airfry at 170c for 10 mins. Give it a toss in between for even cooking.
8. Serve hot with a sprinkle of chat masala, coriander chopped and some lemon wedges.
9. Enjoy!

Air Fryer used @balzano_in

Winter is here!!! ❄️ 
And winter’s without moongdal halwa is incomplete 😋😍

Find the recipe below: 
Recipe: Instant Moong dal halwa
Prep time: 15 mins
Cook time: 40 mins
Servings: 5-6
Blender used: @hamiltonbeachindia jmg
Ingredients:
250 gm Moong dal
¾ cup Ghee + 3 tbsp
1 tbsp suji
1 tbsp Besan
½ cup hot water
500 ml warm milk
2 pinch kesar + 1/4 cup hot water
400 gm sugar
¼ tsp Elaichi powder
¼ cup ghee fried cashews
¼ cup ghee fried almonds
 
 
 
Method:
1. Wash moong dal thoroughly 2-3 times. Let the moong dal drain for 15 minutes.
2. Transfer the drained moong dal into a heavy bottom pan. 
3. Dry roast this over low flame for 10 minutes until the dal turns golden brown.
4. Grind the roasted moong dal to a slightly coarse powder.
5. In a heavy bottom pan add ¾ cup ghee and ground moong dal powder.
6. Roast this until brown over medium low heat for about 10-12 minutes stirring continuously.
7. To this add suji and besan. Sauté for a minute.
8. Add hot water, warm milk, kesar water and sugar. Give it all a good mix and let this cook over medium heat for 20-25 minute while stirring continuously.
9. Cook till the moisture evaporates and the halwa turns deep golden and aromatic.
10. Now add 3 tbsp ghee, Elaichi powder, ghee fried cashews and almonds.
11. Mix well and serve warm.
12. Enjoy!

Healthy and super crispy Sabudana vada anyone?

Recipe: Air fried Sabudana Vada 
Cuisine: Maharashtrian
Prep time: 10 mins
Soak time: 4 hrs
Air fryer: 10 mins
Servings: 2-3
Ingredients:
For Sabudana vada:
 
1 cup Sabudana (washed & soaked for 4 hours and drained)
3 Potatoes (boiled)
¼ cup Peanut (crushed)
5 Green chillies (crushed)
1 tsp Cumin seeds
¼ cup Fresh coriander (chopped)
1 tsp Black/pink Salt 
2 tsp Sugar
 
Cooking spray or 1 tsp Oil
 
Serve with:
Sweetened Curd
Pudina chutney
 
Air fryer used: @balzano_in 
 
Method:
1.  Wash and soak Sabudana for 4 hours. Drain the soaked Sabudana for about an hour.
2.  In a bowl add drained Sabudana, and all the mentioned ingredients except oil.
3.  Give it all a good mix. Grease your palm with a teaspoon of oil. make medium size dough balls and gently flatten the to make vadas.
4.  Pre-heat the Balzano Air fryer 5.5L for 10 minutes at 200 C.
5.  Spray the Basket of the Air fryer with cooking spray or brush some oil. 
6.  Place the Sabudana vadas in the Airfryer.
7.  Spray the vadas lightly with spray oil or brush some oil over them.
8.  Place the basket in the Air fryer and turn on. Cook for 10 minutes at 190 C. 
9.  Flip the vadas half way through. The Air fryer turns on auto automatically when the basket is placed back.
10.  Enjoy non-fried crispy Sabudana vadas with sweetened curd or pudina chutney.

latestIgtvVideos.caption:

Find the recipe and method below:
Recipe: Tandoori Chicken x SS Tikka Tandoor Masala
Prep time: 10 mins
Cook / roast time : 40 mins -1 hr
Servings: 5-6
Ingredients:
1 whole Chicken (1.5 kg)
1 Egg
15 gms/3 tsp Ginger-Garlic paste
100 gms SS tikka Tandoor Masala @ssmasala 
Method:
1. Pre-heat oven at 200 C
2. In a bowl add whole packet of SS Tikka Tandoor Masala, Egg and Ginger-Garlic paste. No need to add salt. Add little water only if required.
3. Give it all a good mix until well combine and forms a thick paste. Set aside.
4. Wash, clean and pat dry 1.5 kg Chicken from outside and inside and remove any excess moisture.
5. Make shallow slits on the chicken so that the marinade can reach inside the chicken.
6. Rub the marinade evenly all over the chicken. Allow the chicken to marinate for at least 30 mins or more in the refrigerator. Bring it to room temperature before roasting.
7. Place the marinated chicken on a wire rack over a roasting pan. Roast at 200 C for about 40 minutes to 1 hour or until the Chicken is cooked through.
8. Once done carefully take the chicken out and brush butter all over the tandoori chicken.
9. Serve with Naan, yogurt-coriander chutney, tomato-onion salad and lemon wedges on the side.
10. Enjoy!!

Jeegujje / Breadfruit podi is a traditional Tulu dish from the coastal region of Karnataka prepared during rainy season 😍
Recipe:
1 jeegujje/ breadfruit
- Peel, remove core and cut into thin strips.
- Soak the sliced pieces in water for 5 minutes.
For the batter:
1 cup besan / chickpea flour
1 cup rice flour
1 tsp chili powder
1/4 tsp hing
1/2 tsp salt (adjust to taste)
1/4 tsp ajwain (crush between palm)
1 & 1/4 cup water (semi thick batter)
- Mix well and prepare a semi thick batter.
- Drain excess water from the soaked jeegujje/breadfruit and add to the prepared batter.
- Heat coconut oil for authentic flavour or any neutral oil.
- Deep fry over medium heat for 2-3 minutes.
- Enjoy immediately with a cup of tea or coffee ☺️

Who said healthy can’t be delicious?
This Juicy Malai Chicken Roast is air-fried, protein-rich, and absolutely addictive! 🍗 😍

Ingredients:
	•	500g skinless chicken thighs
	•	1 tsp ginger garlic paste
	•	½ cup curd
	•	¼ cup fresh cream
	•	1 tsp red chili flakes
	•	1½ tsp coriander powder
	•	½ tsp cumin (jeera) powder
	•	½ tsp kasuri methi
	•	½ tsp black pepper powder
	•	¼ tsp garam masala
	•	½ tsp chaat masala
	•	1 tsp salt (adjust to taste)
	•	1 tsp oil
	•	¼ cup chopped fresh coriander

Method:
	1.	In a bowl, mix chicken with all the ingredients.
	2.	Marinate for at least 30 minutes.
	3.	Place chicken in an air fryer basket.
	4.	Air-fry at 190°C for 9 minutes.
	5.	Flip and cook for another 9 minutes, or until cooked through.
	6.	Serve hot with onion salad (sliced onion + salt + red chili + lemon + coriander)
#summer #rainy #chicken #airfried #airfryer #roast #healthy

Mangalore special Pellakai da mulka 😍
A delicious Mangalore fritter made with ripe jackfruit.
Crispy on the outside, soft on the inside
Ingredient:
Into the blender:
2 cups ripe jackfruit
2 cardamom pods
1 cup grated coconut
1 cup jaggery (adjust to taste)
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 tsp cumin seeds
- blend until smooth
- To this add
1&1/2 cup dosa rice/any raw rice
- soak the rice for 2 hrs and drain to remove excess water
- add to the blended paste and blend until coarse.
- the texture of the batter should be grainy.
- Heat cooking oil preferably coconut oil if you want that authentic taste and aroma.
- Fry on a low to medium heat for 3-4 minutes.
- once cooked through drain excess oil and let it sit for 5-7 minutes before serving.
- Enjoy with some tea or coffee 😊

Summer drinks ep13- Aam panna 
Recipe:
Raw mangoes (about 500 grams)
300 grams jaggery (adjust to taste)
1/2 cup fresh mint leaves
3 teaspoons black salt
3 teaspoons roasted cumin powder
15 black peppercorns
1/2 inch ginger
3 teaspoons soaked fennel seeds
3 cardamom pods
Ice cubes
Instructions:
- Wash the mangoes thoroughly and Place them into a pressure cooker.
- Add 2 cups of water into the pressure cooker along with black peppercorns and ginger.
- Pressure cook the mangoes for 2 whistles. Allow the pressure to release naturally, then let it cool down.
- Once cooled, peel and remove the mango pulp and transfer it into a blender.
- Add jaggery, soaked fennel seeds, 1 cup of the cooked water (along with the cooked peppercorns and ginger), black salt, roasted cumin powder, cardamom pods, and fresh mint leaves.
- Blend all the ingredients together until smooth and well combined.
- Place ice cubes into serving glasses, then pour the Aam Panna.
- Optionally, dilute the Aam Panna with some water to your desired consistency.
- Mix well and enjoy the refreshing Aam Panna to beat the summer heat!
- Leftover Aam Panna can be frozen in an ice cube tray and used as needed. Simply add it into a glass, along with some water, mix, and enjoy anytime 😊
#summer #drink #cool #mango #drinks #healthy #panna

Celebrating Akshay Tritiya with Mango thali 😍✨
1. Kairi Bhaat (Raw Mango Rice)
Ingredients:

* Salt
* Fresh coriander

Method:
Heat oil, Temper mustard seeds, peanuts, dal, chillies, and curry leaves in oil. Add onion, green chilli, and sauté. Add grated mango, spices, mix well. Add rice, stir, garnish with coriander.

2. Sol Kadhi
Ingredients:

* 10 Kokum
* 1/2 tsp Cumin
* 1/4 tsp ajwain
* 3 Garlic sliced
* 1 Green chilli
* Pinch of hing
* 1/4 tsp Salt
* 1/2 tsp Sugar
* 2 cups Water

Method:
Boil kokum in water for 1 minute and let steep. Mix spices, garlic, and kokum water in a bowl. Let it infuse, strain, and serve chilled.

3. Raw Mango Chutney
Ingredients:

* 1 Raw mango
* 1 onion
* 1-2 Green chillies
* 1 inch ginger
* 2 garlic cloves
* 1/4 cup fresh Coriander
* 1/4 cup fresh mint
* 1 tsp Jaggery
* 1/2 salt

Method:
Blend all ingredients into a smooth paste. Chutney is ready.

4. Spicy Aloo Sabzi
Ingredients:

* 3 Boiled potatoes
* 1 Chopped onion
* 2 green chillies
* 1/2 tsp Cumin seeds
* 1/4 tsp hing
* 1 tsp chilli pwd
* 1/4 tsp cumin pwd
* 1/2 tsp coriander pwd
* 1/2 tsp amchur
* Fresh coriander 

Method:
Sauté cumin, onion, and chillies. Add potatoes, spices, mix well, and garnish.

5. Mango Sheera
Ingredients:

* 1 cup Rava (semolina)
* 1/2 cup Ghee
* 1 cup Milk
* 1 cup Mango pulp
* 1/2 cup Sugar
* 1/4 tsp cardamom pwd
* 2 tbsp saffron milk
* Chopped nuts for garnish

Method:
Roast rava in ghee. Add milk, cook till absorbed. Add mango pulp, sugar, cardamom, saffron milk. Cook till fluffy.

6. Amras

Ingredients:

* 3 Ripe Alphonso mango 
* 3 tsp Sugar
* Pinch of Salt
* 1/4 tsp dry ginger/soonth pwd
* 1/4 tsp jaiphal pwd

Method:
Extract mango pulp, strain, mix in sugar and spices. Chill and serve.
